metadata.title: Bowling For Soup - Getting Old Sucks (But Everybodyâ€™s Doing It) [Official Music Video]
metadata.creator: bowlingforsouptv

tracks.text: 2 teenagers in doctors scrubs talk to puppet versions of the band members.
Puppets have an eye and ear exam, get fitted for glasses, and look at a cabinet full of drug bottles.
Drugs labels include "2 a day", "Vitamin B", "Canabys Relaxer", "Fart pills", "Eat this", and question mark.
Puppet Gary plays golf. Puppet Jaret lies on a table with his pants down while someone puts on a glove.
Outside, Jaret gardens
A 5 year old girl smiles at a crayon drawing saying "I love you daddy". She morphs into a teenager.
All the puppets are in bed at 9:00.
The puppets roll down a snowy hill in a carriage.
The puppets play instruments on a stage
The puppets shake their fists at a car driving by
Puppet Gary blows out candles labeled "40". The cake says "Happy birthday old man"
The puppets sit on a stoop, smiling at each other, while holding red solo cups
The puppets fail eye exams
As the puppets play on stage, a young girl sprays hair spray
Text appears. FlashBack to 1985. Caricatures of Jaret, Gary, Chris, and Rob. Rob is a sperm wearing a hat.
The puppets deliver pizza.
Puppet Chris drops to the ground while the others watch and scream. Chris smacks Jaret's leg, and he falls.
Puppets drink in front of grave stones
2 teenagers do a coordinated dance in their kitchen
The puppets play golf, checkers, bingo, and dominos
Puppets hold signs saying "Obey the speed limit", "Slow down", "I want to take a nap", and "Tacos are not just for Tuesday"
The puppets watch the young children play in a band
Puppet Chris strains to see a computer screen, then puts on glasses
The puppets are handed clear cups
They stand side by side at a urinal
Jaret looks right, then left, then gapes
Gary plays drums. Jaret and Rob perform cat pose. Chris lies on his back covered in cookies.
Gary drives down the street
Rob walks in a parking lot
Chris falls head first into a washing machine. The lid closes behind him.
Gary looks at his car's touch screen
Jaret stands over the spinning washing machine and laughs
Rob bends down to pick up a quarter.
Gary selects "A Hangover you don't deserve"
Rob looks up in alarm. Chris emerges from the washing machine and slaps Jaret.
Rob flies onto the hood of Gary's car
The puppets play on stage
They hold protest signs
The puppets sit on a couch and wave to their human counterparts on a zoom call
Jaret flips between channels of Phineas and Ferb, the puppets wearing wigs, and the puppets on stage.
The puppets play on stage
Jaret lies on top of the spinning washing machine
The puppets wear costumes and wigs
The puppets, children, and a puppeteer sing together. The teenage girl is labelled "Puppet Creator"
The puppets sit in lawn chairs in the snow with beer.
Text appears. Blowing for soup. Getting old sucks. Puppets created by Samantha Roche. Directed and edited by Michael Roche.
